    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": "h2",
      "content": "Configuration of the barâ€‹"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "For an example configuration see the supplied defaultsketchybarrc.\nThe configuration file resides in~/.config/sketchybar/sketchybarrcand is a\nregular script that gets executed whenSketchyBarlaunches, everything\npersistent should be set up in this script."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "It is possible to play with properties in the commandline and change\nthem on the fly while the bar is running, once you find a fitting\nvalue you can include it in thesketchybarrcfile, such that the configuration\nis restored on restart. When configuringSketchyBarit can be helpful to stop\nthe brew service and runsketchybarfrom the commandline directly to see all\nrelevant error messages and warnings directly."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "The global bar properties can be configured by invoking:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "where possible settings are:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "You can find the nomenclature for all the typeshere.\nIf you are looking for colors, check out thecolor picker."
    },
